		"Name": "Celerity",
		"Details": "Some mechs can claim to be advanced but few can claim to be as advanced as the Celerity. Developed by ComStar after the Battle of Tukayyid to kickstart their burgeoning drone technology program, the Celerity is the absolute bleeding edge of BattleMech technology. Built on an Endo-Steel frame and equipped with a 240-rated XXL engine which is enhanced by a MASC system, the Celerity is one of the fastest 'Mechs ever produced. However, that speed comes at the cost of armor and firepower: the Celerity has a scant 2.5 tons of armor and has barely any weaponry with only two Small X-Pulse Lasers to defend itself. Because of its tremendous speed, the Celerity is driven via a Drone Operating System that introduces various downsides to the design but given its dedicated role as a recon unit, this was deemed acceptable for the Celerity's envisioned role. The Celerity is tremendously expensive and saw limited deployment.",
